1
00:00:22,360 --> 00:00:24,196
Hurry up. School's over.

2
00:00:24,280 --> 00:00:25,680
We're only late a bit.

3
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:27,240
Le Le won't go anywhere.

4
00:00:27,519 --> 00:00:29,316
I brought you here so that
we could steal the child together.

5
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:30,477
But look at you.

6
00:00:30,560 --> 00:00:31,629
There's no point now.

7
00:00:31,713 --> 00:00:33,793
I'm sure Cheng Ying
has already taken Le Le.

8
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:35,040
We came here for nothing.

9
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:36,077
She's a woman.

10
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:37,680
How could I steal a child from a woman?

11
00:00:38,680 --> 00:00:39,560
Besides,

12
00:00:39,680 --> 00:00:40,757
-it's her child.
-Granny!

13
00:00:40,840 --> 00:00:41,957
Even if you want to steal her child,
you should bring Brother here.

14
00:00:42,040 --> 00:00:43,080
You should tell his father to come.

15
00:00:43,360 --> 00:00:44,440
-Le Le!
-Le Le!

16
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:46,520
Le Le, my baby grandson!

17
00:00:46,640 --> 00:00:47,800
-Come here, Le Le.
-Granny!

18
00:00:49,360 --> 00:00:51,040
Slow down. You'll drop him!

19
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:52,000
Yeah, yeah.

20
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:53,120
Ms Zhang.

21
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:54,757
Le Le's Granny, this weekend,

22
00:00:54,840 --> 00:00:55,757
we need them

23
00:00:55,840 --> 00:00:57,477
to observe lotus leaves and fish

24
00:00:57,560 --> 00:00:58,477
and record them

25
00:00:58,560 --> 00:00:59,997
on their workbook.

26
00:01:00,080 --> 00:01:01,397
We need them to take three photos.

27
00:01:01,480 --> 00:01:03,560
Alright, I'll complete
the task with him.

28
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:05,637
We need his parents to join him.

29
00:01:05,720 --> 00:01:06,557
Not his grandparents.

30
00:01:06,640 --> 00:01:07,560
We want a family photo.

31
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:11,240
He needs to take a photo
with his parents?

32
00:01:12,120 --> 00:01:13,117
Can he take it with his stepmother?

33
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:14,357
Sure.

34
00:01:14,440 --> 00:01:15,237
Le Le's mother called me

35
00:01:15,320 --> 00:01:16,557
and instructed me

36
00:01:16,640 --> 00:01:17,880
to tell you about this.

37
00:01:18,320 --> 00:01:19,360
She called you?

38
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:21,000
Isn't she here today?

39
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:22,437
She said you were coming today.

40
00:01:22,520 --> 00:01:24,400
If you didn't,
I would call her.

41
00:01:25,240 --> 00:01:26,960
Of course I'd be here.

42
00:01:27,440 --> 00:01:28,637
Goodbye, Ms Zhang.

43
00:01:28,720 --> 00:01:29,840
Okay. Take care.

44
00:01:33,240 --> 00:01:34,080
Granny is here.

45
00:01:34,320 --> 00:01:35,477
Baby grandson.

46
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:36,840
Look at what I bought for you. Take it.

47
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:39,000
Didn't your mother come to pick you up?

48
00:01:40,360 --> 00:01:42,037
Mum said I'm going

49
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:43,277
to Dad's house this weekend.

50
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:44,560
She said you would pick me up.

51
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:45,717
Didn't she say anything?

52
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:46,677
Didn't she badmouth

53
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:47,757
your father or me?

54
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:48,677
-Mum!
-She didn't.

55
00:01:48,760 --> 00:01:49,920
You're so narrow-minded.

56
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:51,757
You're badmouthing Sister-in-law

57
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:52,877
and stealing her child.

58
00:01:53,160 --> 00:01:55,320
I told you already. My
sister-in-law isn't that kind of person.

59
00:01:55,401 --> 00:01:56,717
You still brought me here
to do your evil deed.

60
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:57,597
Look at what you've done.

61
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:59,040
I came here for nothing.

62
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:01,797
Listen.
She's just afraid of me.

63
00:02:01,880 --> 00:02:03,160
I have evidence.

64
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:05,117
Listen.

65
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:06,800
I'm sure she's afraid of me.

66
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:08,760
I have evidence.

67
00:02:09,040 --> 00:02:10,957
She's afraid that the court

68
00:02:11,040 --> 00:02:11,837
might give me custody of Le Le

69
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:12,757
when we fight for him.

70
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:13,720
Yeah, yeah.

71
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:15,877
Le Le, can you prove it?

72
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:16,997
Your mother hit me

73
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:18,200
last week, right?

74
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:21,160
You pushed Mum first.

75
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:23,920
Heartless boy.

76
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:25,680
I did it for your sake.

77
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:28,200
Do you know who loves you the most?

78
00:02:28,346 --> 00:02:31,117
Listen.
I'm the one who loves you the most.

79
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:32,397
I was waiting for you

80
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:34,240
in front of the delivery room

81
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:36,040
before you were born.

82
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:38,180
Le Le, don't listen to Granny.

83
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,757
Granny is driving a wedge
between you and your mother.

84
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:41,957
Your mother loves you the most.

85
00:02:42,040 --> 00:02:42,837
Understood?

86
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:44,680
Your grandmother is no match
for your mother.

87
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:48,317
You're so heartless.

88
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:49,317
I was just stating facts.

89
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:50,237
Why are you hitting me?

90
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:51,197
Will you be happy

91
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:52,477
if I say Grandma loves me

92
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:53,400
the most

93
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:54,400
instead of you?

94
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:56,917
Mothers-in-law and daughters-in-law
are born rivals.

95
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:59,080
Even so, you got yourself
two daughters-in-law.

96
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:02,640
It's hard to say. Maybe you'll
get a third one in the future.

97
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:04,040
She'll be my wife.

98
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:05,880
This kid.

99
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:07,640
He has a girlfriend now?

100
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:10,677
When will you bring

101
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:12,400
your girlfriend back?

102
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:13,760
This kid is something else.

103
00:03:13,880 --> 00:03:16,800
(Qibo Medical Centre)

104
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:25,320
What are you doing?

105
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:28,397
-Calm down.
-Tian Zhen!

106
00:03:28,480 --> 00:03:29,960
-What's wrong?
-This is huge.

107
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:31,117
-We're in trouble.
-What is it?

108
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:32,320
Bai Mo Li has a fever, right?

109
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:33,920
How did you know?

110
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:36,037
Don't ask me why. I just know it.

111
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:37,840
Tou Tou, pack your stuff and follow me.

112
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:40,157
Let's go.

113
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:41,080
Wait.

114
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:44,037
Tou Tou.

115
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:44,917
-Mr Ren.
-Coming!

116
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:45,800
She called you?

117
00:03:46,040 --> 00:03:47,000
No.

118
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:48,440
Let's go.

119
00:04:12,040 --> 00:04:13,837
Why did you only tell us by now?

120
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:15,200
It's already the third day.

121
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:17,197
My grandmother didn't tell me
she had a fever

122
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:18,160
on the first day.

123
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:20,237
On the second day, Dr Peng
gave her some medicine.

124
00:04:20,320 --> 00:04:21,600
Her condition didn't
turn for the better after one day.

125
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:23,757
How long has she been taking

126
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:24,720
the new prescription?

127
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,480
She has one more dose left.

128
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:28,880
I've tried all kinds of methods to lower
her body temperature but to no avail.

129
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:30,197
Considering her age,

130
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:31,760
I was planning to send her
to the hospital.

131
00:04:31,880 --> 00:04:33,640
But Mr Ren, she insisted on
bringing you here.

132
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:35,560
That was within my expectation.

133
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:37,677
Did you expect her to vomit blood

134
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:38,640
and have a high fever?

135
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:40,880
Do you really think you're a deity?

136
00:04:42,440 --> 00:04:43,280
Dr Peng,

137
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:45,440
both of us are doctors.

138
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:46,677
You focus on Western medicine

139
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:47,960
while I focus on Chinese medicine.

140
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:50,560
Actually, the field of Western medicine
and Chinese medicine

141
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:52,840
have different explanations
for illnesses.

142
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:55,640
Western doctors like to use

143
00:04:55,960 --> 00:04:57,880
strong words like

144
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:59,840
sedatives and disinfectant

145
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:01,320
to treat illnesses.

146
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:02,400
Actually, illnesses

147
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:04,720
aren't bad things.

148
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:06,357
They're just there

149
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:07,560
to remind our bodies.

150
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:09,320
She's having a fever now.

151
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,317
Actually, it's the conflict

152
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:13,000
between good and bad in her body.

153
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:14,677
To put it bluntly,

154
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:16,320
it's your immunity

155
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:18,320
trying to fight off the invaders.

156
00:05:20,760 --> 00:05:22,037
At her age,

157
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:23,600
it's hard to develop a fever.

158
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:26,200
Try and develop a fever.

159
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:27,917
I think it's been a decade

160
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,960
since you last had a fever.

161
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:32,120
Yeah, I have a healthy body.

162
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:33,200
Not necessarily.

163
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:35,600
There's another type of possibility.

164
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:36,600
It's sub-health.

165
00:05:36,760 --> 00:05:37,637
Actually, his body

166
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:39,520
has already surrendered.

167
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:43,640
If this keeps up,

168
00:05:43,960 --> 00:05:45,560
other complications will occur.

169
00:05:45,960 --> 00:05:47,680
You should stop bragging about
your capabilities.

170
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:50,600
Peng Shi Yan,

171
00:05:50,840 --> 00:05:51,880
mind your words.

172
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:53,440
I've tolerated you for a long time.

173
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:55,720
I know there's a difference
between our fields.

174
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,717
But we should still
respect our teachers.

175
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:59,280
I do respect my teachers.

176
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:00,277
However, there's no difference
between students and teachers

177
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:01,720
when it comes to prudence
towards illnesses.

178
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:03,280
Am I right, Mr Ren?

179
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:05,200
You're right.

180
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:06,840
Madam Bai.

181
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:10,440
Why don't I give you
an acupuncture treatment?

182
00:06:10,960 --> 00:06:11,797
Once it's over,

183
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:13,677
your fever should subside

184
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:15,160
after 45 minutes.

185
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:17,397
Dr Peng made her fever subside.

186
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:19,640
But it came back quickly.

187
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:21,280
Even if he can't do it,

188
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:22,600
that doesn't mean I can't do it.

189
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:26,040
How many needles will you use then?

190
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:28,840
One.

191
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:29,760
Only one?

192
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,400
Yes, only one.

193
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:33,280
And, it doesn't hurt too.

194
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:36,360
Tou Tou,

195
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:38,600
make some porridge for her.

196
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:40,520
She might be hungry after waking up.

197
00:06:40,880 --> 00:06:41,720
Okay.

198
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:49,797
Madam Bai,

199
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:50,677
tell me

200
00:06:50,760 --> 00:06:51,557
if you feel uncomfortable.

201
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:52,600
I'll send you to the hospital.

202
00:06:55,280 --> 00:06:56,280
I'm not going to the hospital.

203
00:06:57,280 --> 00:06:58,840
I want him to treat me.

204
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:01,677
None of us can bear the responsibility

205
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:03,240
if something does happen to you.

206
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:05,400
Dr Peng,

207
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:06,920
you know

208
00:07:07,320 --> 00:07:08,560
that I'm a faithful person.

209
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:12,720
If God is trying to summon me to Heaven,

210
00:07:14,880 --> 00:07:16,120
I will gladly accept it.

211
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:19,680
Madam Bai,

212
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:21,560
I will protect

213
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:22,960
your life.

214
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:24,720
It won't be easy for you to go

215
00:07:25,160 --> 00:07:26,760
when I'm here with you.

216
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:28,840
After the treatment,

217
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:30,720
just close your eyes and rest.

218
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:32,240
It won't hurt at all.

219
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:11,200
You're making porridge?

220
00:08:11,840 --> 00:08:13,000
So, foreigners have rice
in the house too?

221
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:14,160
They don't.

222
00:08:14,880 --> 00:08:15,800
Now, even if your father

223
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:18,357
doesn't tell me anything,

224
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:19,760
I know what to take.

225
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:21,280
I brought it from

226
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:22,480
the medical centre.

227
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:24,197
Not bad at all, bootlicker.

228
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:25,120
Tell me the theory behind it then.

229
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,920
According to the 12th rule of
Treatise On Febrile Caused by Cold,

230
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:29,560
hot porridge should be consumed

231
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:31,440
together with Cinnamon Twig Decoction

232
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,480
to boost its effectiveness.

233
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:34,120
I'm making hot porridge.

234
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:35,360
That's why

235
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:37,320
I brought the Cinnamon Twig Decoction.

236
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:39,600
But your father...

237
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:48,040
Your father didn't say that
he needed it.

238
00:08:49,040 --> 00:08:50,840
I brought it here for nothing.

239
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:52,397
Even now, I still don't understand

240
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:53,757
if your father wishes
to proceed with acupuncture treatment

241
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:54,840
or give her a prescription.

242
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:55,960
Do you have water?

243
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:57,160
I'm thirsty.

244
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:58,800
Yeah. What about some health tea?

245
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:00,600
That'll do.

246
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:01,720
It's inside the bag.

247
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:12,040
How many things have you brought here?

248
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:13,320
At the bottom.

249
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:31,080
You're finally doing decent work now.

250
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:37,160
Remember to insert money
into the money box.

251
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:39,917
You're trying to record your own merit?

252
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:42,277
We should do kind deeds
without expecting anything in return.

253
00:09:42,360 --> 00:09:43,800
We shouldn't bring it up.

254
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:45,637
It's not like I'm bringing it up
on purpose.

255
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:46,757
You'll definitely forget

256
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:48,040
if I don't bring it up.

257
00:09:48,480 --> 00:09:49,360
Can you remember it?

258
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:50,920
Maybe not.

259
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:56,160
Tou Tou.

260
00:10:11,840 --> 00:10:12,840
Send it to your dad.

261
00:10:55,520 --> 00:10:56,440
Her fever has subsided.

262
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:01,040
I'm a little hungry.

263
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:02,960
-You're hungry?
-Here.

264
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:06,640
Feed it to her while it's hot.
Feed her slowly.

265
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:17,960
Has she recovered then?

266
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:21,960
You can take some
Chinese medicine first.

267
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:23,720
After that, you can head to the hospital

268
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:25,480
to get a body check-up.

269
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:26,960
This way, you two

270
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:28,360
can rest at ease.

271
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:29,480
I trust you.

272
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:30,720
I feel relieved

273
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:32,240
since you said that I'm fine now.

274
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:34,197
Thank you for trusting me.

275
00:11:34,280 --> 00:11:35,160
Eat up.

276
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:37,720
Do you admit defeat?

277
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:39,280
Do you?

278
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:41,080
-Eat up.
-Do you admit defeat?

279
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:42,760
I don't.

280
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:44,480
I won't admit defeat.

281
00:11:44,640 --> 00:11:45,677
Listen. We Western doctors

